## Context

RDJ-26561 R&R (tracker 0274), remarks ED-01 (dedup part), R1-12. The referee:
DOI-based dedup misses WP-vs-published pairs (different or absent DOIs);
title+year dedup misses them too (dates and sometimes titles differ). Suggests
incorporating the author variable. Asks for the number of duplicates removed
by each procedure: (1) DOI-based, (2) title+year matching.

## Relevant files

- `deliverables/data-paper/data-paper.qmd` — Method section, dedup paragraph
- Phase-1 dedup implementation in `scripts/` (locate the actual dedup step;
  do not describe from memory)
- `data/catalogs/run_reports/` — may already hold per-step counts

## Actions

1. Extract or instrument per-procedure dedup counts from the Phase-1 pipeline
   (pipeline-traceable numbers only, per the manuscript-number-provenance
   norm; if a Phase-1 rerun is needed, coordinate with the author — it runs
   on padme).
2. Add the counts and an honest discussion of WP-vs-published residual
   duplicates to the paper.
3. Evaluate (possibly as future work rather than implementation) author-aware
   dedup; state the decision and its rationale in the text or response letter.

## Test

- The two counts quoted in the paper match an archived pipeline output.

